not to disturb Mr. Wilson.

358
00:35:03,267 --> 00:35:04,541
l promise.

359
00:35:09,147 --> 00:35:11,138
You know what, Mrs. Wilson?

360
00:35:11,507 --> 00:35:12,542
What?

361
00:35:12,627 --> 00:35:15,425
You're the nicest old gal on the block.

362
00:36:11,187 --> 00:36:12,142
Hello.

363
00:36:13,547 --> 00:36:15,265
My name is Dennis Mitchell.

364
00:36:17,107 --> 00:36:19,746
l'm the doctor. Open up and say....

365
00:36:53,587 --> 00:36:54,542
Hello.

366
00:37:02,347 --> 00:37:03,905
Mr. Wilson.

367
00:37:05,107 --> 00:37:07,223
George? Are you ready?

368
00:37:07,867 --> 00:37:09,778
The photographer's here.

369
00:37:12,787 --> 00:37:14,425
l got a 9:30, ma'am.

370
00:37:14,747 --> 00:37:16,624
He'll be out any second.

371
00:37:17,787 --> 00:37:18,822
Sorry.

372
00:37:22,907 --> 00:37:23,862
George?

373
00:37:30,187 --> 00:37:32,860
That looks fine, Martha. Leave it alone.

374
00:37:34,627 --> 00:37:37,346
Martha, step back. You're in the picture.

375
00:37:40,067 --> 00:37:41,341
Very good.

376
00:37:41,747 --> 00:37:42,896
Now...

377
00:37:43,187 --> 00:37:44,142
smile.

378
00:38:34,387 --> 00:38:36,423
Hey, you.

379
00:38:37,827 --> 00:38:39,738
